by The Soundgebede » Thu Nov 19, 2020 11:41 am

Hitler pretty much faced the same problem Napoleon did. He managed to take Moscow in a mad dash, ignoring the harsh Russian Winter, but Russians -who don't follow Western rules of war- did not surrender upon the fall of Moscow. This meant that the Allies had an opening to march through in the West, leading to the collapse of the Reich and the establishment of a conservative military Junta -still authoritarian, but not as batshit crazy- in Germany during the latter years of the second World War. While Germany still surrendered unconditionally, the USSR could not advance as far west as it did OTL, there were fewer casualties to the Holocaust, and almost all of Germany wasn't utterly wasted as it was OTL.
